unavailable-subtitle: Four hundred people are not summoned with one phone call. (Requires student support.)
on-arrival: sup_students += 3; represion += 2; expediente += 3; political_capital += 2

Four hundred people who received no invitation. The humming becomes singing at the second verse — nobody decides it, it decides itself — and the men photographing from the chapel roof get four hundred faces for their files and one long lesson about arithmetic: they cannot pick up everyone. Not yet.

@intimo
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: unity += 2; political_capital += 1

Nine people and the cypress wind. His mother asks whether it mattered, what he did, and the comrade who answers has the sense to say only: *it is written down. All of it.* The list is the Party's oldest sacrament — kept since the twenties, hidden better than money — because the state's deepest wager is that everyone forgets, and the list is how the wager is lost.
